bilingual.source: No. It was a very small village.
bilingual.target: 不是，那时是个很小的村庄。

bilingual.source: One is big and the other is small.
bilingual.target: 一只是大的，另一只是小的。
这是件很小的运动衫，老板。

bilingual.source: Animals can be big, small, fast or slow.
bilingual.target: 动物可以是大的、小的、快的或慢的。

bilingual.source: The petite very small skater whirled around the rink.
bilingual.target: 那个娇小的滑冰者在冰场上旋转。

这只小的狗叫得很大声。

list.abstract: small（英[smɔːl]，美[smɔːl]），英语单词，作形容词为小型的；不起眼的；极少的。作复数名词为小件衣着用品；小费；小额礼金。作副词为成小块地；小型地；小小地。短语搭配有small talk（闲谈）。例句为“You can also prepare some small gifts for the spouse or kids of the host.（你也可以为主人的配偶或孩子准备一些小礼物。）” small形容词类近义词有little、few等，副词类近义词有basely、contemptibly，名词类近义词有mannie、sparrow，相关反义词有large、big。词根为small。比较级为smaller。最高级为smallest。

yingyinNormal.en: Really? You're changing the Sheldonian calendar? It's a small price to pay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真的吗？你要改谢尔顿日程表？这只是个小小的代价。

yingyinNormal.en: After an appearance in a small cafe in New York City, he made some bad choices.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在纽约的那家小小的咖啡馆露过一次面后，他做了一些错事。

yingyinNormal.en: What a big name for such a small piggy. It's quite nice, even though it's a boy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这么小的宝宝却又这么响亮的名字。名字真不错，虽然他是一个小男孩。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you really have a dog? I do. Named Seamus. He's very small. He's not very smart.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你真的有条狗吗？对啊，它叫塞缪斯，它很小的，不是很机灵。

yingyinNormal.en: But there's a whole table of mini-muffin baskets. Which one did you send? The small one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但桌上全都是英式小松饼，哪一篮是你送的？小的那一篮。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, I want bigger cases too, Grace, but we need to win the small ones to get the big ones.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也想要更大的案子，格蕾丝，但我们得赢了小的才能争取大的。

yingyinNormal.en: At Alibaba, we fight for the little guy, the small businessmen and women and their customers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在阿里巴巴，我们为一些小的生意人，和他们的客户在不懈努力。

yingyinNormal.en: Women have two copies of that big X chromosome; men have the X and, of course, that small copy of the Y.
yingyinNormal.zh: 女性有两条那个大大的X染色体,男性有个X,当然，还有个小小的Y。

yingyinNormal.en: It's difficult to get a booth, finally, we got a small booth. We got the booth, but very few people find us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 找展位很难，最后我们终于找到一个很小的位置，但是很少人光顾。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait. Was this a small Mediterranean guy with curiously intelligent good looks? Yeah, that sounds about right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是不是那个矮小的地中海人，一幅聪明样的帅哥？对，应该就是他。

yingyinNormal.en: These started as small initiatives but have grown beyond any expectations, and continue to transform young people's lives.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们都始于微小的初衷，但却出乎所有人预料的迅速发展，一直在改变和影响着一些年轻人的生活。

yingyinNormal.en: I just need 2,148 high-power lasers to compress 20 micrograms of gold into a small enough volume to make a microscopic black hole.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只需要2148台大功率激光器来把20微克的黄金压缩到足够小的质量从而创造出一个微型黑洞。

yingyinNormal.en: We started detecting gravitational anomalies almost 50 years ago. Mostly small distortions to our instruments in the upper atmosphere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们从五十年前就开始探测到引力异常现象，多数是小的畸变，在大气层上层的仪器中。

yingyinNormal.en: But unless you find a really big tree to sit under, amber preservation will likely remain the domain of insects and other very small animals.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但除非你找到一棵足够大的树，不然琥珀很可能只会保存昆虫和其他很小很小的动物尸体。

yingyinNormal.en: I remember 14 years ago, when I first came to Hannover, I try to rent a small booth to sell the Chinese products to the West and to the Europe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 记得14年以前，我第一次来到汉诺威时，我们试着租了一个小小的展位来出售中国产品到西方，到欧洲。

yingyinNormal.en: The Alamo was a small, isolated fortress with a handful of patriots inside who felt it was important to stick together and fight for what they believed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 阿拉莫曾是一个小小的孤立的城堡，里面住着一些爱国人士，他们团结一心为信念而战。

yingyinNormal.en: Our dreams are very small, aren't they?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的梦想真渺小啊？

yingyinNormal.en: See there it is right there. Wow. It's small.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就在这里。好小。

yingyinNormal.en: And the third reason: Stan has a small wiener.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有第三个原因，斯坦的弟弟超小。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe we shouldn't be taking such small cases.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或许我们不该再接小案子了。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Even dairy farms, where robots do a <highlight>small</highlight> share of milking, have a long way to go before they're automated.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使是机器人只负责一小部分挤奶的奶牛场，在自动化之前也还有很长的路要走。

examination_example.sentence: Instead, being grateful for <highlight>small</highlight> things every day is a much better way to improve wellbeing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相反，每天对小事心存感激是改善幸福感的更好方法。

examination_example.sentence: Conversely, someone with a <highlight>small</highlight> frame may have high body fat but a normal BMI.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相反，身材矮小的人可能体脂高，但身体质量指数正常。

word_usage.usage:
small，little，tiny都有“小的”之意，区别在于：
small多指程度、尺寸等略小于正常的大小。
little指在体积、数量、身材等方面比正常的小，多带主观感情色彩，含小而可爱或小巧的意味。
tiny强调与同类或其他物体比较，小得超出正常比例，含有“微不足道”的意思。

examination_example.sentence: It is a pretty <highlight>small</highlight> industry after all.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毕竟这是一个相当小的行业。

examination_example.sentence: It was only uncovered in relatively recent times that older people's cells divide a <highlight>smaller</highlight> number of times than younger people's.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到最近才发现，老年人的细胞分裂次数比年轻人少。

examination_example.sentence: Others talked about enjoying their own company, of growth through adversity, less judgmental and to listen more and appreciate the <highlight>small</highlight> pleasures.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他的女性则谈到了她们会享受独处，在逆境中成长，减少品头论足，多倾听别人以及享受小乐趣。

word_usage.usage:
small作形容词，表“极少的, 不多的”时，须与不可数名词连用，常用作定语。
示例：They have small hope of succeeding.
他们成功的希望不大。

small与little的区别：
(1) small多用于体积/数量/力量/范围/职位/心胸等，而little多用于年龄/价值/程度/规模等。
示例：This hat is too small for me.
这顶帽子我戴太小。
(2) small不带感情色彩，而little常带有爱怜或赞美等感情色彩。
示例：The little cat is very lovely.
这只小猫真可爱。
